text:
She split from husband of seven years, Michael Mosberg, last year.

And it appears that Girls star Jemima Kirke is moving on as the actress was spotted looking loved-up with Australian singer-songwriter Alex Cameron on Monday.

The 32-year-old star, who has two children with her ex, hung out in New York with the long-haired musician and appeared completely smitten.

His biggest fan: Jemima Kirke appears to be enjoying a new romance with singer Alex Cameron as the duo were spotted together in New York on Monday

Close: The Australian musician was seen embracing the Girls star on the sidewalk

The duo put on quite a tactile display as they embraced on the sidewalk.

It looked as though the mother-of-two was helping Alex with a project, sitting beside him on a subway bench as he promoted his music.

Jemima's ensemble consisted of a white tank top and denim jacket with matching jeans and heavy duty work boots.

Her blonde locks were swept back and she bizarrely appeared to have painted on a hairline to match her beau.

Handsy: The HBO star wrapped her leg around Alex as they stood kissing in the subway

Partner in crime: It looked as though the mother-of-two was helping Alex with a project, sitting beside him on a subway bench as he promoted his music

Smitten: Jemima split from her husband of seven years Michael Mosberg last summer

Quiet moment: The pair looked deep in thought as Alex hugged the British-born actress from behind

Hanging around: Jemima clambered up some scaffolding while clutching a photo of her beau

The Tiny Furniture star was spotted clambering up some scaffolding while holding a picture of the singer.

Jemima reportedly brought Alex as her date to her artist sister Domino's wedding to Gossip Girl alum Penn Badgely last month.

The two said 'I do' for the second time this year at an outdoor ceremony at Lake Waccabuc in upstate New York.

They first wed in a Brooklyn courthouse in February.

Jemima and estranged husband Michael tied the knot in 2009 and separated last summer but their split was only announced in January.

Going solo: The actress shares two daughter with her ex who she married in 2009

Interesting: Jemima appeared to have a bizarre painted-on hairline for the outing, which was likely a project for songwriter Alex

The star's denim jacket featured a cartoon bunny on the back

The duo share daughters Rafaella, six, and son Memphis, four, together.

In February 2016 Jemima revealed to The Telegraph that she met Michael during a rehab stint for 'everything … partying' in her 20s.

She also said that she had started drinking again, socially, a decision her husband was initially worried about.

'Mike was nervous at first. He said, "Look, I would never tell you what to do; you are an adult — just don't f*** it up."

'He had every right to be scared, he knew my story,' she told the newspaper.

'But I was a different person back then. I was in my early 20s. I didn’t have children.'

Heavy duty: Jemima wore double denim with lace-up work boots

Into the sunset: The duo linked arms as they strolled off down the street
